I still remember the morning of my first day at university. I woke up early, 
feeling a mix of excitement and nervousness. I had checked my bag at least 
five times the night before, making sure I had everything ready.

## Arriving at Campus

Walking through the university gates for the first time as a registered 
student felt surreal. The campus was much larger than I had imagined — tall 
buildings, green gardens, and hundreds of students rushing between classes.
https://github.com/raiahmad8882/raiahmad8883.github.io/blob/a3657009d22335d3ee0291802ab90df55641bfdc/assets/images/image-3.jpeg


## My First Lecture

My first class was Introduction to my major subject. The professor walked in 
with a warm smile and said something I will never forget:

> "You are not here just to pass exams. You are here to think, to question, 
and to grow."


> "Those words instantly calmed my nerves and made me feel excited about the 
journey ahead."

## End of Day Thoughts

By the end of that first day, I was exhausted but deeply happy. I had 
attended three classes, explored half the campus, eaten in the cafeteria, 
and already made two new friends. I went home knowing that university was 
going to be the best chapter of my life.
